WEBVTT

00:02.785 --> 00:04.787
[soft music]

00:04.830 --> 00:08.051
- New York City.
Center of the universe.

00:08.095 --> 00:11.185
Home to 8.6 million people.

00:11.228 --> 00:13.535
A diverse melting pot
of culture.

00:13.578 --> 00:16.146
Everyone searching
for meaning and answers.

00:16.190 --> 00:18.279
I thought
I had it all figured out.

00:18.322 --> 00:20.455
But then, something happened,

00:20.498 --> 00:22.587
and it changed
my life forever.

00:22.631 --> 00:25.416
There is no proof of God
anywhere in the universe.

00:25.460 --> 00:27.331
We will debate that and more
on today's episode

00:27.375 --> 00:28.419
of "The Millennial Prophet."

00:28.463 --> 00:30.073
I am your host, Miles Finer,

00:30.117 --> 00:32.684
reminding you that there
is no God, and that is okay.

00:32.728 --> 00:35.252
My guest today
is an old NYU friend,

00:35.296 --> 00:37.733
one of my favorite people.

00:37.776 --> 00:39.517
Ladies and gentleman,
welcome to the podcast

00:39.561 --> 00:41.650
Rabbi Zoe Schwartz.

00:41.693 --> 00:44.305
- Thank you so much
for having me, Miles.

00:44.348 --> 00:46.481
But per usual,
you're misinformed.

00:46.524 --> 00:48.570
There is proof of God
in the Torah.

00:48.613 --> 00:50.267
The miracles of Sinai,
for instance.

00:50.311 --> 00:51.529
You grew up in the church.

00:51.573 --> 00:53.096
You know this better
than anyone.

00:53.140 --> 00:54.880
- Yes, it's true,
my father's a reverend.

00:54.924 --> 00:57.057
We got the whole
Luke/Vader dynamic going on.

00:57.100 --> 01:01.104
But be honest, if I told you
that God sent me a message

01:01.148 --> 01:03.672
in the form a burning bush,
you would think I was insane.

01:03.715 --> 01:05.239
- Not necessarily.
- Oh, come on, Zoe.

01:05.282 --> 01:07.328
- What?
- I understand that

01:07.371 --> 01:09.156
it is comforting to believe

01:09.199 --> 01:10.374
that there is someone
watching over us,

01:10.418 --> 01:12.115
but there is no external force

01:12.159 --> 01:14.204
that's going to reach out
and solve our problems.

01:14.248 --> 01:16.337
- What happened to you, Miles?
- Nothing.

01:16.380 --> 01:17.860
I just want to help people

01:17.903 --> 01:19.644
take responsibility
for their own lives.

01:19.688 --> 01:21.603
I think we would all
be better off if we did.

01:21.646 --> 01:24.388
Hi, Eric.
It's Miles Finer

01:24.432 --> 01:26.216
I was just calling to see
if you had an opportunity

01:26.260 --> 01:27.609
to listen to my podcast.

01:27.652 --> 01:29.698
I think it would
be perfect for Sirius.

01:29.741 --> 01:34.094
Um, you have my phone number,
and my email.

01:34.137 --> 01:37.184
So...yeah.

01:37.227 --> 01:38.359
[laughs]

01:38.402 --> 01:40.143
All right, bye.

01:40.187 --> 01:41.666
- ♪ I'm different,
yeah, I'm different ♪

01:41.710 --> 01:43.320
[phone buzzes]

01:43.364 --> 01:45.583
♪ I'm different,
yeah, I'm different ♪

01:45.627 --> 01:47.194
- [laughs]

01:47.237 --> 01:48.891
What?

01:48.934 --> 01:50.893
[phone buzzes]

01:50.936 --> 01:53.156
- ♪ Pull up to the scene
with my ceiling missing... ♪

01:53.200 --> 01:55.941
- Miles.

01:55.985 --> 01:58.335
Matcha latte.

01:58.379 --> 02:00.294
Hey, man, I checked out
your podcast, bro.

02:00.337 --> 02:03.253
It's dope.
You making a living doing that?

02:03.297 --> 02:04.689
- Yeah, yeah.

02:04.733 --> 02:06.213
I got a ton of listeners,
you know?

02:06.256 --> 02:08.519
Advertising dollars
are really rolling in.

02:08.563 --> 02:10.608
I feel like
I'm making a difference.

02:10.652 --> 02:12.001
And when is the last time

02:12.044 --> 02:13.742
you saw your credit card,
Mr. Johnson?

02:13.785 --> 02:16.353
Well, the only way I can
track it is if they use it.

02:16.397 --> 02:18.921
Yes, it does have a chip.

02:18.964 --> 02:20.618
What am I good for?

02:20.662 --> 02:22.794
Um...

02:22.838 --> 02:24.840
You know,
I've been asking myself that

02:24.883 --> 02:26.189
a lot actually, lately.

02:26.233 --> 02:28.191
Um, I th--

02:28.235 --> 02:30.889
hello?
Hello?

02:30.933 --> 02:34.241
- Do you know how many people
are on the planet, Miles?

02:34.284 --> 02:37.505
- Uh...
- Roughly 7 billion, okay?

02:37.548 --> 02:39.071
You know what the chances are

02:39.115 --> 02:41.291
of finding that one
right person for you?

02:41.335 --> 02:42.771
- Your mom set you up
on another date?

02:42.814 --> 02:44.468
- Yeah, she's obsessed, man.

02:44.512 --> 02:46.470
She's trying to find me
a soul mate again.

02:46.514 --> 02:48.080
I'm like, hello,
there's no such thing,

02:48.124 --> 02:50.735
and she doesn't care,
she just like

02:50.779 --> 02:52.563
"You have
a karmic destiny, Rakesh.

02:52.607 --> 02:54.217
You're to marry
an Indian girl."

02:54.261 --> 02:56.088
I'm like, why can't you just
let me be miserable

02:56.132 --> 02:57.438
on a dating app
like everyone else?

02:57.481 --> 02:59.266
[computer beeps]

02:59.309 --> 03:02.138
- Yo, Eric from Sirius
just emailed me!

03:02.182 --> 03:03.966
- Amazing!
Who's that?

03:04.009 --> 03:05.837
- He's the guy that runs
that podcast channel.

03:05.881 --> 03:08.318
I sent him my show,
and, apparently, he dug it,

03:08.362 --> 03:10.886
and he wants me
to submit a presentation

03:10.929 --> 03:12.409
by Friday
to see where it's headed.

03:12.453 --> 03:13.758
- Miles, you're
about to blow up.

03:13.802 --> 03:16.326
- Mm-hmm.
[laughs]

03:16.370 --> 03:17.849
- You think you'll
get to meet Howard Stern?

03:17.893 --> 03:19.242
- Probably not.

03:19.286 --> 03:21.592
- Congrats on the podcast,
big bro.

03:21.636 --> 03:23.464
- I know you're not down
with the message,

03:23.507 --> 03:25.030
but your support
means everything.

03:25.074 --> 03:28.338
- Mm, that's good to know.
- Mm?

03:28.382 --> 03:29.557
- 'Cause I want you
to do me a favor.

03:29.600 --> 03:31.254
- Yeah, anything.
- Anything?

03:31.298 --> 03:33.430
- Yeah, what's up?
- I want you to come to Dad's

03:33.474 --> 03:35.824
25th at the church this Sunday.
- Anything but that.

03:35.867 --> 03:37.521
- The two of you
haven't spoken in months.

03:37.565 --> 03:39.523
Come on, this is
the perfect opportunity

03:39.567 --> 03:41.264
for you two
to start talking again.

03:41.308 --> 03:43.005
- Why do I have
to take the first step?

03:43.048 --> 03:45.703
If Dad wanted me there,
he would have invited me.

03:45.747 --> 03:47.270
- Of course Dad
wants you there.

03:47.314 --> 03:49.881
You know every Sunday
after church,

03:49.925 --> 03:52.319
he goes to St. Nicholas park.
- So he goes to play chess.

03:52.362 --> 03:53.711
- He goes there because
that's where

03:53.755 --> 03:56.061
the two of you used to play.

03:56.105 --> 03:58.586
Look, Miles,
what is it going to take

03:58.629 --> 04:00.457
to bring the two of you
back together?

04:02.067 --> 04:03.939
- [exhales]

04:03.982 --> 04:08.291
Look, sis, I have to get home
and finish this presentation.

04:08.335 --> 04:11.033
Thanks for the beer.
- Anytime.

04:14.645 --> 04:16.081
[phone buzzes]

04:16.125 --> 04:18.258
[tense music]

04:18.301 --> 04:19.955
[phone beeps]

04:19.998 --> 04:27.005
♪

04:37.277 --> 04:38.974
[phone beeps]

04:39.017 --> 04:41.803
[phone buzzes]

04:41.846 --> 04:45.067
[fire crackles]

04:45.110 --> 04:47.025
- Holy.

04:48.505 --> 04:50.377
- Hey!
Damn kids.

04:50.420 --> 04:53.336
You come around here again,
I'll call the police!

04:53.380 --> 04:55.251
[fire extinguisher whooshes]

04:55.295 --> 04:57.297
[phone buzzes]

05:04.216 --> 05:06.567
[phone buzzes]

05:06.610 --> 05:09.744
- Who's John Dove?

05:09.787 --> 05:12.790
- Stacy, wait, please!
- Whoa!

05:12.834 --> 05:16.054
- I am so sorry.
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

05:16.098 --> 05:18.013
Stacy, hold on.
Hey, hey, hey, wait.

05:18.056 --> 05:19.493
Wait, just give me
one more chance.

05:19.536 --> 05:21.582
Just talk to me.
- You've changed, John.

05:21.625 --> 05:23.540
I'm sorry, it's over.

05:23.584 --> 05:30.591
♪

05:47.172 --> 05:49.087
[train rails screeching]

05:51.612 --> 05:55.485
- Hey, John Dove!
Hey!

06:02.013 --> 06:04.494
[train honking]

06:09.586 --> 06:11.719
Hey, hey,
somebody stop that guy!

06:14.286 --> 06:17.333
Whoa, what the hell, man?

06:17.377 --> 06:20.510
Are you okay?

06:20.554 --> 06:22.556
- Yeah.

06:23.731 --> 06:25.689
I think you just saved my life.

06:25.733 --> 06:28.649
[soft music]

06:28.692 --> 06:30.999
Thank you.

06:31.042 --> 06:38.049
♪

06:43.751 --> 06:45.753
- [exhales]

07:00.724 --> 07:04.511
- Yeah, oh, no, Miles, hey.
That guy was not going to jump.

07:04.554 --> 07:05.947
No, no, no, no, no.

07:05.990 --> 07:07.601
This is all
just some elaborate hoax.

07:07.644 --> 07:09.254
That's what it is.

07:09.298 --> 07:10.995
[heavy breathing]

07:11.039 --> 07:12.867
Yeah, yeah.

07:12.910 --> 07:15.870
[tense music]

07:15.913 --> 07:22.920
♪

07:26.097 --> 07:28.448
Nice try.

07:33.017 --> 07:34.845
Oh, come on.

07:37.021 --> 07:39.023
Yo, who the hell is Cara Bloom?

07:39.067 --> 07:42.026
[tense music]

07:42.070 --> 07:43.637
♪

07:43.680 --> 07:45.813
- Cara.
- Uh, hey.

07:45.856 --> 07:47.771
- In my office, now.

07:49.469 --> 07:50.731
Do you see the hotboard?

07:50.774 --> 07:52.384
You used to have
the top trending stories

07:52.428 --> 07:54.386
on our site every week.
- Yeah, yeah, I know.

07:54.430 --> 07:56.214
And I'll get back there,
I promise.

07:56.258 --> 07:58.521
- I don't want promises,
I want articles.

07:58.565 --> 08:00.523
You haven't written one
in six weeks.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.133
- I'm just working
through a rough patch.

08:02.177 --> 08:03.657
You know, it took Hemmingway
ten years

08:03.700 --> 08:05.920
to write his second novel.
- Is that true?

08:05.963 --> 08:07.704
- I think.

08:07.748 --> 08:10.272
- Look, I don't know what's
going on with you lately,

08:10.315 --> 08:12.056
but I can't cut you
any more slack.

08:12.100 --> 08:14.494
I want a story
by the end of the week.

08:14.537 --> 08:16.408
And it goes without saying,

08:16.452 --> 08:19.455
this is one of those
"or else" situations.

08:19.499 --> 08:21.544
- Let me
get this straight, okay?

08:21.588 --> 08:23.633
You're being catfished
by someone

08:23.677 --> 08:25.505
calling themselves God
on Facebook.

08:25.548 --> 08:27.376
- Yes, and I need your
hacker skills

08:27.419 --> 08:29.334
to get me their IP address.
- Bro, keep your voice--

08:29.378 --> 08:32.555
how many times I got to
tell you I'm not a hacker?

08:32.599 --> 08:34.688
Okay, I'm a
video game enthusiast.

08:34.731 --> 08:37.168
Plus, you said it yourself,
it's just a prank.

08:37.212 --> 08:40.345
So focus on your presentation.
- I will, but first,

08:40.389 --> 08:41.651
I've got to figure out
who's behind this.

08:41.695 --> 08:42.957
- Why?

08:43.000 --> 08:44.698
So they're trolling you.
Let it go.

08:44.741 --> 08:47.352
- I believe everything in life
can be explained.

08:47.396 --> 08:49.616
That there is no God,
and there is someone out there

08:49.659 --> 08:51.095
who is going through
a whole lot of trouble

08:51.139 --> 08:53.315
to prove me wrong.
I can't let that go.

08:55.317 --> 08:57.319
- Okay, you really think
someone paid this Dove guy

08:57.362 --> 08:58.886
to pretend to jump
in front of that train?

08:58.929 --> 09:01.628
- Yes, what other explanation
is there?

09:01.671 --> 09:03.804
It's like "The Game."

09:03.847 --> 09:07.198
- Oh, great flick.
Early Fincher.

09:07.242 --> 09:08.939
Okay, what do you know?

09:08.983 --> 09:11.115
- Okay, I looked into
John Dove's Facebook account.

09:11.159 --> 09:14.379
It's a ghost town.
My only lead?

09:14.423 --> 09:16.077
Cara Bloom.

09:16.120 --> 09:17.469
- Okay, what do you
know about her?

09:17.513 --> 09:19.080
- Come see for yourself.

09:19.123 --> 09:22.344
She went to Ohio State,
writes for "Catapult,"

09:22.387 --> 09:26.914
and runs marathons.
- Cute and accomplished, bro!

09:26.957 --> 09:28.916
Why can't I ever match
with someone like her?

09:28.959 --> 09:31.222
- This isn't Tinder, Rakesh.
- You mean Bumble, bro.

09:31.266 --> 09:33.181
Nobody uses Tinder anymore.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.879
- Look, she just checked in
to SoulCycle.

09:35.923 --> 09:37.533
I'm going to go down there,

09:37.577 --> 09:39.317
and I'm going to
get to the bottom of this.

09:39.361 --> 09:41.102
[groovy music]

09:41.145 --> 09:44.584
- That's a bad idea, Miles.

09:44.627 --> 09:47.456
What are you going to tell her?
God sent you?

09:48.936 --> 09:50.764
[both laugh]

09:50.807 --> 09:52.635
- I can't feel my legs,
but my ass looks great.

09:52.679 --> 09:54.245
So, fair trade.
- Yeah, it does.

09:54.289 --> 09:55.333
I got to run to Trader Joe's.
See you later?

09:55.377 --> 09:57.422
- Yeah, see you.

09:57.466 --> 10:00.034
- ♪ Lips became your body,
nice turned into naughty ♪

10:00.077 --> 10:03.690
♪ You hit me
with a plot twist ♪

10:03.733 --> 10:08.216
- Cara, Cara!
Miles Finer.

10:08.259 --> 10:09.609
- Uh--
- Oh, come on.

10:09.652 --> 10:11.175
Don't act like
you don't know who I am.

10:11.219 --> 10:14.352
- I don't, so have a nice day.

10:14.396 --> 10:16.398
- Wait, are you God?
- Excuse me?

10:16.441 --> 10:18.487
- I mean, not like "the" God.
There is no God.

10:18.530 --> 10:20.620
I just really want to know
who's behind the God account.

10:20.663 --> 10:22.447
- The God account?
What are you talking about?

10:22.491 --> 10:24.754
- Wow, you are
a committed actor.

10:24.798 --> 10:26.843
What, did you study with
Stella Adler or something?

10:26.887 --> 10:29.193
- Look, I don't know what
you're on, but I carry mace.

10:29.237 --> 10:30.586
- And I work at IdentitySeal,

10:30.630 --> 10:32.022
so you tell
whoever's behind this

10:32.066 --> 10:34.242
I will jack up their credit!

10:34.285 --> 10:37.027
[exhales]

10:37.071 --> 10:39.421
Be glad you didn't grow up
with social media.

10:39.464 --> 10:42.424
[tense music]

10:42.467 --> 10:43.773
♪

10:43.817 --> 10:47.647
Delete, delete.
Good-bye.

10:47.690 --> 10:49.866
♪

10:49.910 --> 10:54.001
It's time to refocus, and get
this presentation to Sirius.

10:54.044 --> 11:01.051
♪

11:12.193 --> 11:14.717
["Human" by Rag'n'Bone Man]

11:14.761 --> 11:18.199
- ♪ I'm only human after all

11:18.242 --> 11:21.202
[heavy breathing]

11:21.245 --> 11:23.595
- What the?

11:27.556 --> 11:28.905
What the hell?

11:28.949 --> 11:31.734
[beeping]

11:31.778 --> 11:34.389
- ♪ I'm only human after all

11:34.432 --> 11:37.044
♪ I'm only human after all

11:37.087 --> 11:39.002
♪ Don't put the blame on me

11:39.046 --> 11:41.396
[computer beeps]

11:43.615 --> 11:45.487
[tense music]

11:45.530 --> 11:47.010
[computer beeps]

11:47.054 --> 11:54.061
♪

11:58.892 --> 12:00.720
- You want to believe
in the heavenly father

12:00.763 --> 12:03.548
- No, my presentation!
- Deep down, I know you do.

12:03.592 --> 12:04.941
- Oh, no, no, no,
my presentation!

12:04.985 --> 12:06.377
- Behold his mighty hand!

12:06.421 --> 12:07.814
[computer beeps]

12:07.857 --> 12:10.120
- No.

12:10.164 --> 12:13.471
No, no, no, no!
Come on, no!

12:13.515 --> 12:15.256
Where's my presentation?

12:15.299 --> 12:17.127
[grunts]

12:26.833 --> 12:29.792
[groovy music]

12:29.836 --> 12:33.013
♪

12:33.056 --> 12:35.885
- How do you cure
writer's block?

12:46.243 --> 12:48.637
- Cara.

12:48.680 --> 12:49.638
- What the hell
are you doing here?

12:49.681 --> 12:51.379
- This has gone too far.

12:51.422 --> 12:54.034
Hacking my computer,
my presentation, my thermostat.

12:54.077 --> 12:55.818
Who is behind the God account?

12:55.862 --> 12:58.734
- Listen, I don't know anything
about the God account.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.083
Or the temperature
in your apartment,

13:00.127 --> 13:01.519
or how did you
even get back here?

13:01.563 --> 13:02.956
- Are they paying you
for this, huh?

13:02.999 --> 13:04.261
Are you writing a story
about it?

13:04.305 --> 13:06.176
- A story.
Yeah, I'm staring at

13:06.220 --> 13:08.048
a blank page and my career
is hanging in the balance,

13:08.091 --> 13:12.530
so I would say no.
- You're telling the truth?

13:12.574 --> 13:14.141
You're not in on any of this?

13:14.184 --> 13:16.752
- I don't even know
what this is.

13:16.796 --> 13:19.146
[soft music]

13:19.189 --> 13:21.278
- [exhales]

13:21.322 --> 13:27.197
♪

13:27.241 --> 13:30.853
- Hey, you okay?
- It doesn't make any sense.

13:30.897 --> 13:32.681
Why would they send me
your name?

13:32.724 --> 13:34.683
- Wait, what do you mean
send you my name?

13:34.726 --> 13:36.511
- Look.

13:38.252 --> 13:39.993
- Wait, so someone
calling themselves God

13:40.036 --> 13:41.690
sent you
a friend suggestion for me?

13:41.733 --> 13:44.301
- Look, I know how it sounds,
but yes.

13:44.345 --> 13:46.608
- Cara, where's my story?

13:46.651 --> 13:50.438
- Uh, I am working on it.
Making progress.

13:50.481 --> 13:52.396
- Who is this?

13:52.440 --> 13:54.703
- This is someone that I'm
interviewing for my story.

13:54.746 --> 13:58.185
- Really?
What's it about?

13:58.228 --> 14:00.361
- Well, it's
a think piece about

14:00.404 --> 14:02.667
the intersection
of faith and science

14:02.711 --> 14:04.408
through the prism
of social media.

14:04.452 --> 14:07.063
It's going to be great.

14:07.107 --> 14:10.284
- I like it.
I want 1,000 words tomorrow.

14:15.680 --> 14:18.858
- Hey, I did not say you can
write a story about this.

14:18.901 --> 14:21.338
- Yeah, well,
this isn't just about you.

14:21.382 --> 14:23.645
Look, they sent you
my name, too.

14:23.688 --> 14:25.473
You want to figure out
who's screwing with you.

14:25.516 --> 14:27.910
I'm a journalist.
I know how to find people.

14:27.954 --> 14:30.521
And I will...

14:30.565 --> 14:32.393
but only if I get the story.

14:32.436 --> 14:34.874
- You find them...

14:34.917 --> 14:36.745
we talk.

14:36.788 --> 14:38.225
- Deal.

14:38.268 --> 14:39.922
So I assume you've looked into
this God account.

14:39.966 --> 14:41.793
What do you know?
- Not much.

14:41.837 --> 14:44.318
I tried to get my boy, Rakesh,
to find me the IP address,

14:44.361 --> 14:46.624
but he won't do it for me.

14:46.668 --> 14:50.063
♪

14:50.106 --> 14:52.326
But he might do it for you.

14:54.632 --> 14:56.112
[doorbell buzzes]

14:56.156 --> 14:58.723
- Rakesh, the door.
- Got it, Mom.

15:01.683 --> 15:04.729
- Cara, Rakesh.
Rakesh, Cara.

15:04.773 --> 15:08.124
- Hey.
- Hi.

15:08.168 --> 15:10.257
What is she doing here?

15:10.300 --> 15:12.259
- She can hear you.
- Right.

15:12.302 --> 15:14.696
- She's not involved.
I told her everything.

15:14.739 --> 15:16.480
She's going to help me
figure out who's behind this.

15:16.524 --> 15:20.615
But we need a favor
from you, first.

15:20.658 --> 15:23.748
- Uh, this is
my workout attire.

15:23.792 --> 15:25.054
[sniffs]

15:25.098 --> 15:27.013
I do 60 crunches
every morning, so.

15:27.056 --> 15:28.840
- Look, I know
you're not a hacker,

15:28.884 --> 15:30.973
but if there's any way you
can get us that IP address--

15:31.017 --> 15:34.020
- No, guys, I'm a hacker.
[chuckles]

15:34.063 --> 15:36.370
I'm a badass hacker, actually.

15:36.413 --> 15:38.981
[tense music]

15:39.025 --> 15:41.679
Guys, this can't be right.

15:41.723 --> 15:43.116
The God account's
being protected

15:43.159 --> 15:44.856
by a firewall
I've never seen before.

15:44.900 --> 15:46.249
- Don't mess with me.
- I'm not messing with you.

15:46.293 --> 15:48.860
Man, this code is sublime.

15:48.904 --> 15:52.212
Like, there's only a small pool
of people on the planet

15:52.255 --> 15:53.735
who could've written
something like this.

15:53.778 --> 15:55.171
- So there's no way
to track the IP address?

15:55.215 --> 15:56.694
- No, I said small pool.

15:56.738 --> 15:59.828
Lucky for you guys,
I'm swimming in it.

15:59.871 --> 16:01.264
Okay, here's the thing though.

16:01.308 --> 16:04.006
If what I see here is right,

16:04.050 --> 16:06.878
there's a good chance that Dove
guy really was going to jump.

16:06.922 --> 16:08.271
- Explain.

16:08.315 --> 16:09.620
- It's called
predictive analytics.

16:09.664 --> 16:10.752
It's a type of AI
used to determine

16:10.795 --> 16:12.275
the outcome of events.

16:12.319 --> 16:14.451
So theoretically,
someone with this technology

16:14.495 --> 16:16.453
could have just know Dove
was depressed and suicidal.

16:16.497 --> 16:17.889
- Even if what
you're saying is true,

16:17.933 --> 16:19.282
there's no way
they could have known

16:19.326 --> 16:20.631
that I would have
stepped in and saved him.

16:20.675 --> 16:22.459
- Unless that's the point
of it all.

16:22.503 --> 16:24.331
To see if you would.

16:26.594 --> 16:28.291
I really think
you saved this guy.

16:28.335 --> 16:31.294
[tense music]

16:31.338 --> 16:32.948
♪

16:32.992 --> 16:34.950
- Look, we need to find
this Dove guy.

16:34.994 --> 16:36.473
My money says he's in on it.

16:36.517 --> 16:38.998
- Yeah, but our best lead
is this IP address.

16:39.041 --> 16:40.651
How long would it take you
to crack it?

16:40.695 --> 16:42.349
- I don't know, man.
I'll keep working on it,

16:42.392 --> 16:45.700
but I have a date
in a few hours.

16:45.743 --> 16:49.791
She's not my girlfriend.
I'm totally single.

16:49.834 --> 16:52.315
My mom's making me go.

16:52.359 --> 16:54.535
- Oh, I have to redo
my presentation

16:54.578 --> 16:57.886
for Sirius by tomorrow,
and this thing is spiraling.

16:57.929 --> 16:59.322
- Is he always this dramatic?

16:59.366 --> 17:01.063
- Oh, you should see him
at a Yankees game.

17:01.107 --> 17:02.934
- Al, you sure this isn't
one of your psych experiments?

17:02.978 --> 17:04.501
Right before God friended me,

17:04.545 --> 17:06.460
you were trying to convince me
to go see Dad.

17:06.503 --> 17:09.202
- Miles, I am not behind this.
You know I detest social media.

17:09.245 --> 17:11.595
- Wait, what happened
with you and your Dad?

17:11.639 --> 17:13.510
- Nothing.
- Our dad is a reverend.

17:13.554 --> 17:15.947
Miles is an atheist.
You do the math.

17:15.991 --> 17:18.037
- That explains a lot.
- Wait a minute.

17:18.080 --> 17:20.039
You don't think Dad
is behind this, do you?

17:20.082 --> 17:23.259
- Really, Miles?
He can't even use Netflix.

17:23.303 --> 17:25.392
You know
what's happening to you

17:25.435 --> 17:26.741
is kind of like
the prodigal son,

17:26.784 --> 17:28.656
except God is using Facebook

17:28.699 --> 17:29.657
to bring you and Dad
back together.

17:29.700 --> 17:31.137
- Do you see what growing up

17:31.180 --> 17:32.660
in a house of religion
does to the mind?

17:32.703 --> 17:35.097
- She makes a good point.
- Thank you.

17:35.141 --> 17:37.099
- So you believe in God?

17:37.143 --> 17:38.709
- I mean, I wouldn't say
that I'm religious,

17:38.753 --> 17:42.148
but yeah, I am spiritual.
- Oh, boy, here we go.

17:42.191 --> 17:43.845
- Spiritual.

17:43.888 --> 17:46.413
You mean the biggest cop out
in all of religion?

17:46.456 --> 17:47.544
- What?
- Well, you can't have

17:47.588 --> 17:49.111
one foot in the eternal plane,

17:49.155 --> 17:50.112
and the other
in the "I'm cool" category.

17:50.156 --> 17:51.461
It doesn't work like that.

17:51.505 --> 17:53.463
You either believe
or you don't.

17:53.507 --> 17:57.337
- Or you recognize that there's
something greater at work here.

17:57.380 --> 18:00.296
I don't know, some grand design
connecting us all.

18:00.340 --> 18:02.733
Otherwise, life just seems
kind of pointless.

18:02.777 --> 18:04.953
- I like her.
- Trust me.

18:04.996 --> 18:06.302
There is no grand design.

18:06.346 --> 18:07.825
[phone beeps]

18:07.869 --> 18:11.046
Whoa, Rakesh.
Tell me you got something.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.353
- Miles, I did it.
I found God.

18:13.396 --> 18:15.050
He's in Jersey.

18:15.094 --> 18:17.096
[groovy music]

18:23.667 --> 18:25.408
- Wait, look,
the house is for sale.

18:25.452 --> 18:26.583
- Well, Rakesh
tracked them here.

18:26.627 --> 18:27.758
Someone's inside.

18:27.802 --> 18:29.499
[tense music]

18:29.543 --> 18:32.415
- So how does a preacher's son
lose his faith in God?

18:32.459 --> 18:34.461
- Pretty easily.
- Wait, let me guess.

18:34.504 --> 18:35.679
You felt religion was forced

18:35.723 --> 18:37.159
down your throat,
so you rebelled.

18:37.203 --> 18:39.509
Got your hands
on Hitchens and Dawkins,

18:39.553 --> 18:40.684
never looked back?

18:40.728 --> 18:45.167
- Yeah, something like that.

18:45.211 --> 18:48.475
- Oh, I don't know.
Maybe God moved.

18:53.349 --> 18:55.656
Oh, hey, look.
There's a light on over here.

18:55.699 --> 18:57.266
[knocks on door]
- All right, come on.

18:57.310 --> 18:58.659
Open up.
Open up.

18:58.702 --> 19:00.878
You're messing
with the wrong guy.

19:00.922 --> 19:03.316
- Uh, step aside.

19:06.754 --> 19:08.495
Give me some light.

19:08.538 --> 19:11.498
[tense music]

19:11.541 --> 19:16.459
♪

19:16.503 --> 19:18.679
What?
- Nothing.

19:18.722 --> 19:21.116
Just admiring your skills.
What, did you write an article

19:21.160 --> 19:22.683
about picking locks
or something?

19:22.726 --> 19:24.337
- Eh, it was more of a PSA
on how easy it is

19:24.380 --> 19:25.729
to break into your own house.

19:25.773 --> 19:27.949
It went viral in like,
15 minutes.

19:30.299 --> 19:32.040
[lock clicks]

19:35.174 --> 19:37.480
- What?

19:37.524 --> 19:38.786
That is impressive.

19:38.829 --> 19:40.483
- Thank you.

19:40.527 --> 19:43.573
Hey, you got a plan, right?

19:43.617 --> 19:45.488
Because I'm guessing
whoever's up there,

19:45.532 --> 19:47.838
they don't want to be found,
and they might not be friendly.

19:47.882 --> 19:50.406
- Trust me.
I got a plan.

19:50.450 --> 19:53.409
[tense music]

19:53.453 --> 20:00.460
♪

20:09.860 --> 20:12.385
Hey, it's Miles Finer.

20:12.428 --> 20:15.823
I know you're in there.
Come out now.

20:15.866 --> 20:17.738
- Great plan.

20:32.927 --> 20:34.624
- [exhales]

20:36.017 --> 20:38.411
- Yeah, so much for
the light of God.

20:41.065 --> 20:44.373
This was a bogus lead.

20:44.417 --> 20:47.898
- Or maybe not.
Look at this.

20:47.942 --> 20:49.378
[tense music]

20:49.422 --> 20:51.685
- Yeah, it's Jersey.
They're tacky.

20:51.728 --> 20:54.253
- No, whoever's behind this
knew I would end up here.

20:54.296 --> 20:56.820
That angel might as well be
giving me the middle finger.

20:56.864 --> 20:58.779
- That's ridiculous.
They're painting over it

20:58.822 --> 21:00.171
because they're
selling the house.

21:00.215 --> 21:03.305
- No, I got a bad feeling
about this.

21:03.349 --> 21:05.699
[bright piano music]

21:05.742 --> 21:07.440
♪

21:07.483 --> 21:10.312
- The food is really good.
- Yeah, yeah, it is, yeah.

21:10.356 --> 21:12.227
[phone dings]

21:15.317 --> 21:18.320
- Important message?
- Um, it's a friend of mine.

21:18.364 --> 21:21.105
He's in Jersey looking for God.

21:21.149 --> 21:23.238
- [laughs]

21:23.282 --> 21:24.805
You're funny.

21:26.154 --> 21:28.461
Most of the guys my parents
set me up with are total bores.

21:28.504 --> 21:30.027
- Yeah, you know, honestly,

21:30.071 --> 21:31.638
I don't know why
they've got to do this to us.

21:31.681 --> 21:33.727
I mean, we're perfectly capable
of deciding

21:33.770 --> 21:35.294
who we want
to fall in love with.

21:35.337 --> 21:37.034
I mean, don't get me wrong,
you're gorgeous,

21:37.078 --> 21:38.993
but I'm sure there are
plenty of other guys out there

21:39.036 --> 21:40.647
you'd rather be on a date with.

21:40.690 --> 21:43.780
- Actually,
I'm enjoying myself.

21:43.824 --> 21:47.175
And I think you're pretty cute.

21:47.218 --> 21:49.133
- Okay.

21:49.177 --> 21:50.874
- You know what I like to do
to get back at my parents?

21:50.918 --> 21:52.398
- What?

21:52.441 --> 21:54.965
- Things they wouldn't
approve of.

21:56.706 --> 21:59.927
- I--oh--uh.

21:59.970 --> 22:02.190
I also like to do those things.

22:02.233 --> 22:04.932
- It's too bad we both
live at home.

22:13.680 --> 22:15.638
[soft music]

22:15.682 --> 22:17.510
♪

22:17.553 --> 22:21.122
- I called a Lyft.
Tina, Ford Fusion.

22:21.165 --> 22:23.472
Four minutes away.

22:25.909 --> 22:28.564
Hey, you okay?

22:28.608 --> 22:30.653
- It's weird, I had
the same exact bench

22:30.697 --> 22:32.829
on my front porch growing up.

22:34.614 --> 22:37.747
Every day,
I'd sit there, just...

22:37.791 --> 22:39.836
waiting for--

22:39.880 --> 22:41.577
- Waiting for what?

22:43.449 --> 22:45.059
- Uh, nothing.

22:45.102 --> 22:47.714
- It doesn't
look like nothing.

22:47.757 --> 22:50.412
[phone buzzes]

22:50.456 --> 22:52.196
Hey, Rakesh, what's up?
- You need to get back

22:52.240 --> 22:53.981
to your apartment like,
right now, man.

22:54.024 --> 22:56.244
I think Mr. Robot
hacked your computer again.

22:56.287 --> 22:57.898
- Wait, dude, why are you
at my apartment?

22:57.941 --> 22:59.290
["Human" by Rag'n'Bone Man]

22:59.334 --> 23:01.380
- Not important.
Stay focused.

23:01.423 --> 23:03.599
Man, your iPhoto library
is on loop.

23:03.643 --> 23:05.427
The same song is playing
over and over.

23:05.471 --> 23:08.212
Even I can't make it stop.
- What song?

23:08.256 --> 23:10.780
- ♪ I'm only human after all

23:10.824 --> 23:11.999
♪ I'm only human after all

23:12.042 --> 23:13.435
- Yeah, I already tried that.

23:13.479 --> 23:16.264
My guess is they used
a smurf attack.

23:16.307 --> 23:18.397
- Your pictures
are really great.

23:18.440 --> 23:21.008
♪

23:21.051 --> 23:22.879
- [mouthing words]
- [gasps]

23:22.923 --> 23:24.446
- How many times
I got to tell you,

23:24.490 --> 23:26.448
you got to switch your Wi-fi
to WPA2.

23:26.492 --> 23:28.058
- You just pull the plug.
- No, no.

23:28.102 --> 23:30.539
There has to be a reason
why they're doing this.

23:30.583 --> 23:32.280
[music stops]

23:32.323 --> 23:34.848
- How'd you get it to stop?
- I didn't.

23:34.891 --> 23:37.851
[tense music]

23:37.894 --> 23:41.463
♪

23:41.507 --> 23:43.160
- Uh, you know, I just
remembered I'm on deadline,

23:43.204 --> 23:45.206
so uh, I got to go.

23:48.209 --> 23:50.646
- Cara, hold up.

23:50.690 --> 23:52.779
Hey, what's going on?

23:52.822 --> 23:54.824
- Nothing, I'm fine.
- Cara, is everything okay?

23:54.868 --> 23:57.000
- Yeah, I just--
I need to finish my story.

23:57.044 --> 23:58.741
I'll see you later.

24:00.830 --> 24:02.919
- What was that all about?
- I don't know.

24:02.963 --> 24:05.139
- She got really weird
when she saw the photo.

24:05.182 --> 24:08.577
- Yeah, but why?
It's just you and your family.

24:08.621 --> 24:10.449
- My mom's doctor and nurse.

24:10.492 --> 24:12.973
It was right after my mom
had her last chemo.

24:13.016 --> 24:14.975
[soft music]

24:15.018 --> 24:16.890
- What?

24:16.933 --> 24:18.674
♪

24:18.718 --> 24:20.502
You think she knows
one of them?

24:20.546 --> 24:23.200
You remember their names?
- I was eight.

24:28.467 --> 24:30.947
But there is one person
who may know.

24:30.991 --> 24:34.385
[women vocalizing]

24:34.429 --> 24:38.085
- God is always testing us,

24:38.128 --> 24:39.739
and we know this
from the Book of James,

24:39.782 --> 24:42.306
Chapter 1, Verse 12.

24:42.350 --> 24:45.658
"Blessed is he who remains
steadfast under trial,

24:45.701 --> 24:47.964
"for when
he has stood the test,

24:48.008 --> 24:51.185
he will receive
the crown of life."

24:53.796 --> 24:56.016
- You getting ready for Sunday?

24:57.539 --> 25:00.063
- Miles.

25:00.107 --> 25:03.763
- I used to love
listening to your sermons.

25:03.806 --> 25:05.678
I would sneak in
to the back of the chapel

25:05.721 --> 25:08.158
and watch you practice.

25:08.202 --> 25:11.466
That's until Mom caught me
and made me do my homework.

25:11.510 --> 25:14.600
- I remember.
What are you doing here?

25:14.643 --> 25:17.472
- I need your help
with something, um...

25:17.516 --> 25:18.908
[phone clicks]

25:20.301 --> 25:24.523
Do you remember
Mom's doctor and nurse?

25:25.741 --> 25:28.744
- Um...

25:28.788 --> 25:32.226
What's this about?
- I just need their names.

25:33.793 --> 25:38.449
- Sure, son.
Um...

25:38.493 --> 25:42.497
This is Dr. John Andrews,
and his nurse, Susan Albright.

25:42.541 --> 25:45.544
They took great care
of your mother.

25:46.675 --> 25:49.243
- Thank you.
- Hey, Miles, wait.

25:53.813 --> 25:55.336
[exhales]

25:55.379 --> 25:58.948
I've been meaning to reach out
to you about Sunday.

25:58.992 --> 26:02.952
Um, the church is celebrating
my 25 years here, and...

26:05.085 --> 26:06.782
I'd like you to come.

26:06.826 --> 26:09.480
- It's a good thing
I stopped by so you can ask me.

26:09.524 --> 26:10.917
- I deserved that.
I should have called.

26:10.960 --> 26:14.224
I guess I was afraid
that you'd say no.

26:14.268 --> 26:15.748
- Or maybe you were afraid
that you would be judged

26:15.791 --> 26:17.488
because your son
doesn't believe in God?

26:17.532 --> 26:19.316
- And what am I supposed
to feel about that?

26:19.360 --> 26:22.624
I--I've devoted my life to God,

26:22.668 --> 26:25.148
and you spread the notion
that he doesn't exist.

26:25.192 --> 26:29.326
I--I--I know you think
you're helping people,

26:29.370 --> 26:31.372
but you're not.
- That's not true.

26:31.415 --> 26:32.678
- Name one person.

26:32.721 --> 26:34.767
One person
who's life you changed.

26:34.810 --> 26:36.986
- It's a podcast, Dad.
I don't have to see the person

26:37.030 --> 26:38.422
to know that I am
making a difference.

26:38.466 --> 26:40.990
- You are taking away
people's hope.

26:41.034 --> 26:43.079
- And you're lying to them!

26:43.123 --> 26:45.038
You're telling them that God
is watching over us.

26:45.081 --> 26:47.910
You know better than anyone
that's not true.

26:47.954 --> 26:51.392
- What I know is...

26:51.435 --> 26:52.828
Is that you're angry.

26:52.872 --> 26:55.048
[soft music]

26:55.091 --> 26:57.354
You don't think that
what happened

26:57.398 --> 26:59.574
made me
question my faith?

26:59.618 --> 27:04.579
♪

27:04.623 --> 27:06.450
What I also know is,
is that we can't

27:06.494 --> 27:09.671
keep having this argument.

27:09.715 --> 27:11.847
- Yeah.

27:11.891 --> 27:14.545
Yeah, you're right about that.

27:25.731 --> 27:29.517
- Want to talk about it?
- Not really.

27:29.560 --> 27:31.650
- Also, if you're still mad
at me for hooking up

27:31.693 --> 27:34.478
with Jaz at your place, you're
kind of missing the point.

27:34.522 --> 27:37.699
- No, I'm not mad,
but please enlighten me.

27:37.743 --> 27:39.353
- If we don't
go back to your place,

27:39.396 --> 27:41.398
I don't call you about God
hacking your computer,

27:41.442 --> 27:44.097
and Cara doesn't see the doctor
and the nurse in the photo.

27:44.140 --> 27:46.708
So if you think about it...

27:46.752 --> 27:48.318
I'm kind of the hero
of this story.

27:48.362 --> 27:50.886
[both laugh]

27:50.930 --> 27:52.758
- Okay, here we go.

27:52.801 --> 27:56.457
Into the Department of Records.

27:56.500 --> 27:59.982
It says Dr. Andrews moved out
of the city years ago.

28:00.026 --> 28:01.854
- Okay, try Susan Albright.

28:01.897 --> 28:04.726
[tense music]

28:04.770 --> 28:06.336
♪

28:06.380 --> 28:09.078
- Moved from Ohio to New York
18 years ago.

28:09.122 --> 28:13.169
Changed her name.
it used to be Susan Bloom.

28:17.043 --> 28:19.349
- She's Cara's mom.

28:27.793 --> 28:29.011
["Helium" by Sia]
- ♪ I'm trying

28:29.055 --> 28:32.014
♪ But I keep falling down

28:32.058 --> 28:33.842
♪

28:33.886 --> 28:39.326
♪ I cry out,
but nothing comes now ♪

28:39.369 --> 28:41.763
- Hell of a view.

28:43.809 --> 28:46.246
- Uh, yeah, yeah.
I love it up here.

28:46.289 --> 28:48.988
- Your roommate told me
that you were up here.

28:50.772 --> 28:52.905
- Hey, sorry for
running out last night.

28:52.948 --> 28:55.255
I was just stressed about work.

28:55.298 --> 28:57.736
- Look, I know the nurse
in the photo is your mom.

29:00.782 --> 29:03.959
She left when you
were a kid, right?

29:04.003 --> 29:05.787
That's who you were waiting for
on the bench?

29:05.831 --> 29:08.181
- Uh, I don't--I don't really
want to talk about this.

29:08.224 --> 29:10.661
- Come on, your mom and my mom
were in the same photo.

29:10.705 --> 29:12.402
What are the odds?

29:12.446 --> 29:14.317
That must be the reason
why they sent me your name.

29:14.361 --> 29:15.666
- Miles.
- They want me to help you

29:15.710 --> 29:17.843
find her--
- Miles, you're wrong.

29:17.886 --> 29:20.802
- How can you say that?
- Because I already found her.

29:20.846 --> 29:22.456
[tense music]

29:22.499 --> 29:24.110
- When?

29:24.153 --> 29:26.590
- Six weeks ago.

29:26.634 --> 29:28.462
On the subway.

29:31.247 --> 29:33.336
She was sitting
right across from me.

29:33.380 --> 29:36.078
♪

29:36.122 --> 29:38.341
Um...

29:38.385 --> 29:40.779
Look, you were right.

29:40.822 --> 29:44.521
My mom did leave
when I was seven.

29:46.697 --> 29:48.525
And then,
a couple months later,

29:48.569 --> 29:49.918
she came back,

29:49.962 --> 29:54.314
and she told my dad
that she'd gotten sober.

29:54.357 --> 29:57.143
But then, a few months
after that, she left for good.

29:57.186 --> 29:58.840
All I knew was that
she came to New York,

29:58.884 --> 30:02.365
so after college,
I came here looking for her.

30:02.409 --> 30:05.281
But nothing ever came of it
until I saw her that day.

30:09.285 --> 30:13.768
- What did you say to her?
- Nothing.

30:13.812 --> 30:16.205
Nothing, I just--I froze.

30:17.903 --> 30:22.211
And when she got off
the train, I...

30:22.255 --> 30:23.996
I followed her
to St. Vincent's Park,

30:24.039 --> 30:27.695
and I sat there, watching her.

30:31.699 --> 30:33.266
I don't know, I guess I--

30:33.309 --> 30:34.658
I thought I would
work up the nerve

30:34.702 --> 30:37.270
to say something to her,
but I didn't.

30:37.313 --> 30:40.403
And I have gone back
pretty much every day since

30:40.447 --> 30:42.318
at the exact same time,

30:42.362 --> 30:44.364
and I sit on the
exact same bench,

30:44.407 --> 30:46.845
but every time...

30:46.888 --> 30:48.759
I lose my nerve.

30:50.152 --> 30:51.501
And ever since I saw her,

30:51.545 --> 30:54.374
I can't--I can't sleep,
I can't write.

30:54.417 --> 30:55.375
- But don't you see?
That's why you

30:55.418 --> 30:56.985
have to go talk to her.

30:57.029 --> 30:59.466
Things won't get better
unless you do.

30:59.509 --> 31:01.860
- Why do you even care?

31:01.903 --> 31:04.775
You're just trying to figure
out who's behind all of this.

31:04.819 --> 31:06.734
- That's not true.

31:06.777 --> 31:09.737
[soft music]

31:09.780 --> 31:11.870
♪

31:11.913 --> 31:15.917
You asked me why
I don't believe in God.

31:15.961 --> 31:19.878
When--when I was eight,

31:19.921 --> 31:22.837
my mother was diagnosed
with breast cancer,

31:22.881 --> 31:26.580
and the doctor said she had
six months to live.

31:26.623 --> 31:30.801
And so I prayed for a miracle,
and then it happened.

31:30.845 --> 31:32.238
She went into full remission.

31:32.281 --> 31:34.196
The doctors couldn't even
explain it.

31:34.240 --> 31:36.329
- I don't understand.
If God answered your prayers,

31:36.372 --> 31:38.592
why don't you believe?

31:40.768 --> 31:43.031
- Because on the way home
from the hospital,

31:43.075 --> 31:44.990
she died in a car accident.

31:47.514 --> 31:51.213
- Miles.
I am so sorry.

31:51.257 --> 31:53.476
- I tried to make sense of it,

31:53.520 --> 31:56.349
and the only way I could

31:56.392 --> 31:58.612
was that there was no God.

31:58.655 --> 32:01.223
Because if there was,
that means that he is cruel,

32:01.267 --> 32:02.355
and I don't want
to live in a world

32:02.398 --> 32:04.183
governed by someone like that.

32:04.226 --> 32:06.228
[soft music]

32:06.272 --> 32:08.709
Look, I don't know
who's behind this,

32:08.752 --> 32:11.581
or why they chose me.

32:11.625 --> 32:15.281
But I do know that your mom
is still out there,

32:15.324 --> 32:19.459
and you can still have
a relationship with her.

32:19.502 --> 32:22.592
I'd give anything
to say the same.

32:22.636 --> 32:25.204
- Yeah, but what if she wants
nothing to do with me?

32:26.335 --> 32:28.511
- Then you know,

32:28.555 --> 32:31.079
and you can finally move on.

32:31.123 --> 32:38.130
♪

32:43.265 --> 32:45.485
- Um...

32:47.400 --> 32:49.141
There she is.

32:49.184 --> 32:50.403
- [sighs]

32:50.446 --> 32:52.231
Okay.

32:52.274 --> 32:54.885
You can do this, yeah?
- Yeah.

32:54.929 --> 32:57.801
- I'll be right here.

32:57.845 --> 32:59.542
Unless I get hungry,
then I'll be

32:59.586 --> 33:01.109
across the street
getting a churro.

33:01.153 --> 33:03.459
[both laugh]

33:03.503 --> 33:06.332
You got it.
- Okay.

33:29.224 --> 33:32.184
[soft music]

33:32.227 --> 33:33.620
♪

33:33.663 --> 33:37.015
- Hi.
- Hello.

33:51.377 --> 33:54.119
- It's a really nice day.

33:54.162 --> 33:56.121
- Yeah, it is.

34:12.050 --> 34:14.443
Cara?

34:14.487 --> 34:16.054
- Hi, Mom.

34:17.838 --> 34:19.231
- How?

34:19.274 --> 34:22.756
- It's a long story.

34:22.799 --> 34:26.716
I heard you became a nurse.
That's--that's good.

34:26.760 --> 34:30.546
♪

34:30.590 --> 34:32.200
- Cara.

34:32.244 --> 34:35.377
♪

34:35.421 --> 34:38.641
- Why didn't you come home?

34:38.685 --> 34:41.688
- I tried, but I couldn't.

34:41.731 --> 34:44.560
- Then you should have
tried harder.

34:44.604 --> 34:47.433
- Please let me explain.
- No.

34:48.695 --> 34:50.262
No.

34:50.305 --> 34:53.787
I grew up thinking
that you hated me.

34:53.830 --> 34:55.223
I spent years in therapy

34:55.267 --> 34:57.182
trying to figure out
what I did wrong.

34:57.225 --> 35:00.141
I deserve a better answer
than "I tried."

35:00.185 --> 35:02.883
- Mom?

35:02.926 --> 35:04.450
Is everything okay?

35:06.756 --> 35:08.367
- Oh, no.

35:14.112 --> 35:16.766
- Guess that answers that.

35:18.899 --> 35:20.770
- Cara, wait.

35:24.426 --> 35:26.385
- Cara!

35:28.561 --> 35:30.476
- [sobs]

35:30.519 --> 35:33.087
- Cara!

35:33.131 --> 35:34.480
[horn honks]

35:34.523 --> 35:38.179
Cara!
Cara!

35:38.223 --> 35:40.834
- She came out of nowhere.
- Call 911!

35:40.877 --> 35:43.010
Cara, stay with me.
Stay with me, Cara.

35:43.053 --> 35:44.490
Stay with me.

35:44.533 --> 35:46.056
Oh, no, no, no.
She's not breathing.

35:46.100 --> 35:48.189
What's taking so long, man?
- I'm on hold.

35:48.233 --> 35:51.192
[tense music]

35:51.236 --> 35:53.977
♪

35:54.021 --> 35:55.196
- John Dove?

35:55.240 --> 35:57.155
- You're the guy
from the subway.

35:58.243 --> 36:00.549
- She needs a doctor.

36:00.593 --> 36:01.942
- I am a doctor.

36:01.985 --> 36:04.858
[dramatic music]

36:04.901 --> 36:11.908
♪

36:20.439 --> 36:23.224
We got a pulse.
- [exhales]

36:23.268 --> 36:26.227
♪

36:26.271 --> 36:32.233
♪

36:32.277 --> 36:34.235
- I just spoke
with the attending.

36:34.279 --> 36:36.019
Cara's resting.
It wasn't pretty.

36:36.063 --> 36:38.457
She has a punctured lung,
and a couple bruised ribs,

36:38.500 --> 36:39.632
but she's going to be okay.

36:39.675 --> 36:41.199
- [exhales]

36:41.242 --> 36:42.852
That's good.

36:42.896 --> 36:46.465
So you just so happened
to be driving by

36:46.508 --> 36:49.076
at that very moment?
No one put you up to it?

36:49.119 --> 36:51.600
- Put me up to what?
What are you talking about?

36:51.644 --> 36:53.950
- Just a hell of a coincidence,
you being a doctor.

36:53.994 --> 36:58.346
- Well, technically,
I'm not anymore.

36:58.390 --> 36:59.913
After what happened
on the subway,

36:59.956 --> 37:02.829
I decided to take a leave.

37:02.872 --> 37:07.268
♪

37:07.312 --> 37:09.966
I had just lost a patient
on the table.

37:10.010 --> 37:13.231
My girlfriend broke up with me.

37:13.274 --> 37:15.842
It felt like an avalanche.

37:15.885 --> 37:17.974
When you pulled me back...

37:19.324 --> 37:22.196
I realized, you know,
I didn't want to die.

37:25.808 --> 37:28.289
- That's good.

37:28.333 --> 37:30.683
And for what it's worth,

37:30.726 --> 37:33.947
you seem like
a very good doctor to me.

37:36.341 --> 37:38.343
- Thank you.

37:40.301 --> 37:41.259
- [mouths]

37:42.477 --> 37:44.436
How are you feeling?

37:44.479 --> 37:47.917
- Like I got hit by a car
really hard.

37:47.961 --> 37:49.658
- Thought I lost you there.

37:49.702 --> 37:52.139
- I'm still here,
thanks to you.

37:52.182 --> 37:54.359
- Mm.
- Uh, you saved John Dove,

37:54.402 --> 37:56.230
and he saved me.

37:56.274 --> 37:59.102
If you think about it, it's
kind of like a grand design.

38:01.279 --> 38:03.498
Have you heard anything
about your podcast?

38:03.542 --> 38:05.761
- I didn't turn it in.
- What?

38:05.805 --> 38:08.721
- I couldn't leave without
knowing that you were okay.

38:08.764 --> 38:11.158
[knocking]

38:11.201 --> 38:13.247
You have somebody
here to see you.

38:16.119 --> 38:17.730
- Hi.

38:19.166 --> 38:21.560
- You called her?

38:22.952 --> 38:26.304
- I'll wait outside.
- No, wait, you stay.

38:31.265 --> 38:32.875
What do you want?

38:32.919 --> 38:35.922
- You asked me why
I never came back.

38:37.532 --> 38:39.665
I did.

38:39.708 --> 38:42.624
- What?
- You were in eighth grade.

38:42.668 --> 38:44.670
I came to one
of your track meets.

38:44.713 --> 38:46.889
♪

38:46.933 --> 38:49.327
You were running the 400.

38:49.370 --> 38:52.330
That was my race
in high school.

38:52.373 --> 38:55.942
You won, and I saw you.

38:55.985 --> 39:00.381
You looked so happy,
so confident.

39:00.425 --> 39:02.514
- Why didn't you say anything?

39:04.429 --> 39:07.214
- I was afraid...

39:07.257 --> 39:11.740
If I came back, and things
didn't work out again,

39:11.784 --> 39:15.353
it would shatter you forever.

39:15.396 --> 39:18.573
And I couldn't
take that chance.

39:18.617 --> 39:20.270
So I walked away.

39:20.314 --> 39:22.229
- [exhales]

39:25.363 --> 39:28.888
- I've thought about
that moment every day since.

39:30.455 --> 39:34.850
Hoping one day
I might get another chance.

39:37.462 --> 39:40.290
So I just want you to know,

39:40.334 --> 39:43.163
if you'd let me...

39:48.298 --> 39:50.518
I want to be
a part of your life.

39:51.780 --> 39:53.565
- [exhales]

39:53.608 --> 39:56.959
- People say that God
has a plan for all of us.

39:57.003 --> 39:59.353
That we're all part
of a grand design.

39:59.397 --> 40:02.008
Well, I never believed that
to be true,

40:02.051 --> 40:04.445
but then, he friended me,

40:04.489 --> 40:07.056
and it kind of turned my life
upside down.

40:07.100 --> 40:08.406
Not that I think it's God,

40:08.449 --> 40:11.278
but in these crazy times
we live in,

40:11.321 --> 40:14.281
we owe it to ourselves
to ask the tough questions,

40:14.324 --> 40:18.764
and to open our minds to
a new way of seeing the world.

40:18.807 --> 40:21.680
A place where we can
find our voice again.

40:21.723 --> 40:25.466
- Top story on the board.
Impressive work.

40:25.510 --> 40:27.729
Don't make me wait six weeks
for the next one.

40:27.773 --> 40:30.340
- ♪ And I am steadfast

40:30.384 --> 40:32.647
- Where old wounds can heal,

40:32.691 --> 40:34.475
and new relationships
can begin.

40:34.519 --> 40:36.738
- Hi.
- Liv.

40:36.782 --> 40:39.872
This is your sister, Cara.

40:39.915 --> 40:42.527
- Hi, Liv.
It's nice to meet you.

40:42.570 --> 40:44.442
- Nice to meet you, too.

40:44.485 --> 40:46.487
♪

40:46.531 --> 40:49.098
- Where we finally understand
our purpose.

40:49.142 --> 40:51.492
♪

40:51.536 --> 40:54.887
And find love
in the most unexpected place.

40:58.673 --> 41:00.022
- The world we live in today

41:00.066 --> 41:02.982
asks more of us now
than ever before.

41:03.025 --> 41:06.594
It demands more of us.
Why?

41:06.638 --> 41:08.944
Because as our minds
and our hearts

41:08.988 --> 41:13.471
and our ambitions flourish,
so too, the roads to sin.

41:14.733 --> 41:16.996
- It's not going to be easy.

41:17.039 --> 41:19.477
Change never is.

41:22.828 --> 41:24.525
We just need
to have the courage

41:24.569 --> 41:27.615
to take the first step.

41:27.659 --> 41:30.357
- ♪ And I am desperate

41:30.400 --> 41:33.752
♪ And all that I dream

41:33.795 --> 41:37.190
♪ Where do you run?

41:37.233 --> 41:39.192
♪ Where do you run to?

41:39.235 --> 41:42.587
♪ Carrier, friend

41:42.630 --> 41:45.024
♪ Where do you run?

41:45.067 --> 41:47.896
- I read your story
about finding your sister.

41:47.940 --> 41:50.246
It was really touching.
- Thank you.

41:50.290 --> 41:52.597
- Yeah, and I appreciate you
not mentioning

41:52.640 --> 41:54.120
the whole God account thing.

41:54.163 --> 41:56.339
- Yeah, you know,
it was never my story to tell.

41:56.383 --> 41:57.732
Besides, I actually
really loved

41:57.776 --> 41:59.908
how you talked about it
on your podcast.

41:59.952 --> 42:03.216
- Wait, you listened
to my podcast?

42:03.259 --> 42:05.261
- Maybe.

42:05.305 --> 42:06.959
- You're not the only one.

42:07.002 --> 42:09.135
Eric from Sirius listened
to it, and he loved it.

42:09.178 --> 42:10.658
- What?
- And he wants to meet.

42:10.702 --> 42:12.442
- Miles, that's amazing.
- Yeah.

42:12.486 --> 42:15.097
- I'm so happy for you.

42:16.229 --> 42:19.624
So, um, have you heard anything
from the God account?

42:19.667 --> 42:22.583
- Uh, not since they
sent me your name, why?

42:22.627 --> 42:24.063
- Well, just because I told you

42:24.106 --> 42:26.195
I'd help you
get to the bottom of it.

42:26.239 --> 42:28.328
So I will.

42:28.371 --> 42:30.504
["Ways To Go" by Grouplove]

42:30.548 --> 42:33.725
Besides, maybe we'll do
some good in the process.

42:33.768 --> 42:36.771
Actually make a difference
in some people's lives.

42:36.815 --> 42:38.120
- Yeah, that wouldn't be
so bad.

42:38.164 --> 42:40.601
- ♪ Been working like a dog

42:40.645 --> 42:42.995
- Oh, uh, I have to go.

42:43.038 --> 42:45.127
My sister has a soccer game.
That's crazy, right?

42:45.171 --> 42:47.260
- Yeah, yeah, go do your thing.

42:47.303 --> 42:50.132
- Okay, whenever you hear from
the God account, text me.

42:50.176 --> 42:52.961
♪

42:53.005 --> 42:55.007
[phone buzzes]

42:56.965 --> 42:59.359
[phone beeps]

42:59.402 --> 43:01.666
- ♪ I've got
a little bit longer ♪

43:01.709 --> 43:03.711
- ♪ I've got a ways to go

